---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The Breakthrough - Greenfield Platform"
  description="Why software development has been fundamentally broken and how bounded contexts solve the cognitive overload problem universally."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-400 to-purple-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
            The Breakthrough
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Why software development has been fundamentally broken and how we've discovered the universal solution
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Problem Section -->
        <section class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-blue-400">The Fundamental Problem</h2>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-red-400">Dual Cognitive Overload</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Software development is broken because both AI and humans hit cognitive limits. When AI tries to understand
              too much context, it makes mistakes. These mistakes cascade into overwhelming amounts of work for humans to fix.
              It's a vicious cycle where overloaded AI creates problems that overload humans.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-400 mr-3">•</span>
                <span>AI loses accuracy with large contexts, generating flawed code</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-400 mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Humans can't review AI output fast enough to catch all issues</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-400 mr-3">•</span>
                <span>Mistakes compound: bad AI suggestions lead to rushed human fixes</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-400 mr-3">•</span>
                <span>More context makes AI hallucinate, not help</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-red-400 mr-3">•</span>
                <span>The cascade effect: confused AI → bad code → overwhelmed humans → more confusion</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Solution Section -->
        <section class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-green-400">The Universal Solution</h2>
          <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-400">Bounded Contexts</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
              The breakthrough isn't a new technology—it's a new way of thinking. Bounded contexts solve the dual cognitive overload
              by creating clear, isolated domains that keep both AI and humans operating at peak performance. Small contexts mean
              accurate AI output and manageable human review.
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-blue-400">Perfect Isolation</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-300">
                  Each context is completely self-contained. AI stays focused and accurate. Humans only review manageable chunks.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-400">Universal Application</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-300">
                  Works for any project: greenfield startups, 15-year legacy systems, enterprise applications.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-yellow-400">Effortless Scaling</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-300">
                  Add new features without touching existing code. Scale teams without coordination overhead.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-pink-400">Fearless Development</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-300">
                  Limited scope prevents AI hallucinations. Isolated changes mean controllable impact.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Why It Works Section -->
        <section class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-purple-400">Why This Works for Everything</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-blue-400">Any Project Size</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-300">
                From solo projects to enterprise systems with millions of users. Bounded contexts scale infinitely
                because they divide complexity instead of adding to it.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-400">Any Project Age</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-300">
                Brand new greenfield projects and 15-year legacy monoliths. The approach works by creating new
                bounded contexts that gradually absorb complexity from existing systems.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-yellow-400">Any Technology Stack</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-300">
                Language and framework agnostic. Bounded contexts are a thinking pattern, not a technology constraint.
                Use whatever tools work best for each context.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- CTA Section -->
        <section class="text-center">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600 rounded-lg p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Experience the Breakthrough?</h2>
            <p class="text-lg mb-6 opacity-90">
              See the proof in real production systems and learn how to apply this to your projects.
            </p>
            <div class="space-x-4">
              <a href="/proof" class="inline-block bg-white text-blue-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-slate-100 transition-colors">
                See the Proof
              </a>
              <a href="/platform" class="inline-block border-2 border-white text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-white hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">
                Explore the Platform
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>